## How to prevent functional/class components from unnecessary re-rendering?
- in the functonal 
    - components: we can use React.memo to wrap up the component, only re-render when the props has changes
    - useCallback: remember the function definition, avoiding the new function as props to sent to the child component
    - useMemo : manage and remember the expensive result or object, ensure the stability

- Class Component
    - Pure Component will compare the props and statement shallowly. similar to React.memo
    - shouldComponentUpdate
